  "texts": [
    "Hence, 1 //A fancy string is a string where no three consecutive characters are equal.",
    "2 Given a string s, delete the minimum possible number of characters from s to make it fancy.",
    "3 Return the final string after the deletion.",
    "It can be shown that the answer will always be unique.",
    "4 public String makeFancyString(String s) { 5 StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(s); 6 for (int i = 2; i < sb.length(); i++) { 7 if (sb.charAt(i) == sb.charAt(i-1) && sb.charAt(i) == sb.charAt(i-2)) { 8 sb.deleteCharAt(i); 9 -i -= 2; 10 + i -= 1; 11 } 12 } 13 return sb.toString(); 14 } Fig. 3."
  ],
